29 SECTION 9, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
30 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) Upon petition by any person and after a
31 hearing under IC 29-3-5, the court may issue, without the appointment
32 of a guardian, any protective order for the benefit of a person who has
33 been adjudicated an incapacitated person or is a minor.
34 (b) Notice of the filing of a petition under this chapter for the
35 issuance of a protective order and the hearing on the petition shall be
36 given under IC 29-3-6.
37 (c) Incapacitated persons and minors have the same rights at the
38 hearing on a petition filed under this chapter for the issuance of a
39 protective order as they would have at a hearing for the appointment of
