1 (1) the incapacitated person:
2 (A) owns property or has income requiring management or
3 protection that cannot otherwise be provided;
4 (B) has or may have financial or business affairs that may be
5 jeopardized or impaired; or
6 (C) has property that needs to be managed to provide for the
7 support or protection of the incapacitated person;
8 (2) the incapacitated person is unable to manage the incapacitated
