1 SECTION 11. IC 32-17-8-4.5 IS ADDED TO THE INDIANA
2 CODE AS A NEW SECTION TO READ AS FOLLOWS
3 [EFFECTIVE JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 4.5. For all purposes under this
4 chapter and IC 30-4-5-26, this section applies only to a lifetime or
5 inter vivos transfer of property to a trust or similar arrangement
6 under which the spouse of the transferor is granted a limited power
7 of appointment ("earlier power") that can be exercised during the
8 spouse's lifetime or upon the spouse's death to create a subsequent
9 limited power of appointment or another nonvested property
10 interest. The exercise of the earlier power or another nonvested
11 property interest is considered to have been created at the time of
12 the creation of the earlier power by the transferor.
13 SECTION 12. IC 32-28-15-1, AS ADDED BY P.L.62-2024,
14 SECTION 1, IS AMENDED TO READ AS FOLLOWS [EFFECTIVE
15 JULY 1, 2026]: Sec. 1. (a) Except as otherwise provided in this
16 chapter, this chapter does not apply to a residential real estate service
17 agreement entered into before March 15, 2024.
18 (b) This chapter does not apply to any of the following:
19 (1) A home warranty or similar product that covers the cost of
20 maintenance of a major home system, such as:
21 (A) a plumbing system;
22 (B) a heating, cooling, and ventilation system; or
23 (C) electrical wiring;
24 for a fixed period.
25 (2) An insurance contract.
26 (3) An option to purchase residential real estate or a right of
27 refusal to purchase residential real estate.
28 (4) A declaration that is created in the formation of:
29 (A) an association of co-owners (as defined in IC 32-25-2-2)
30 for a condominium (as defined in IC 32-25-2-7); or
31 (B) a homeowners association (as defined in IC 32-25.5-2-4);
32 including any amendment to the declaration.
33 (5) A maintenance or repair agreement entered into by:
34 (A) an association of co-owners (as defined in IC 32-25-2-2)
35 for a condominium (as defined in IC 32-25-2-7); or
36 (B) a homeowners association (as defined in IC 32-25.5-2-4).
37 (6) A mortgage loan or a commitment to make or receive a
38 mortgage loan.
39 (7) A security agreement under IC 26-1 concerning the sale or
40 rental of personal property or fixtures.
41 (8) Providers of:
42 (A) utility services, including water, sewer, gas, or electric
